  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Up to date, devices capable of delivering controlled, calibrated, non-contact cold air
      stimuli in a MR environment are unavailable for quantitative sensory testing. This project
      therefore aimed at designing and constructing a novel MR-compatible, computer-controlled cold
      air stimulation device that produces air puffs in a broad flow and cold temperature range. By
      means of this device, detailed psychophysically testing and subsequent brain scanning of
      dentine hypersensitivity (DH) subjects will be possible to gain new insights about DH
      mechanisms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
